    description: `The Chadar Trek is one of the most unique and exhilarating expeditions in the world — a winter walk on the frozen surface of the Zanskar river in Ladakh. Undertaken only in January and February when temperatures plunge to −20°C and below, the trek follows the river canyon through a landscape of frozen waterfalls, ice sculptures, and sheer cliff faces. The name 'Chadar' means 'sheet' in Hindi, referring to the flat sheet of ice that forms over the river. Villages like Tibb and Naerak, otherwise inaccessible in winter, are reached on foot. This is a physically demanding, logistically complex expedition that demands acclimatisation, the right gear, and a high tolerance for extreme cold — and rewards those who attempt it with an otherworldly experience.`,
