    description: `Bhrigu Lake is one of Himachal Pradesh's most rewarding alpine lake treks, a vivid blue tarn at 4,300 metres above the Kullu valley that offers unobstructed views of the Rohtang range and the Pir Panjal. The approach from Vashisht near Manali climbs through dense mixed forest into rolling high-altitude meadows — Rola Kholi and the vast Bhrigu meadows — before the final ascent to the lake. What makes Bhrigu unique is the quality of the meadow trekking: for hours before reaching the lake, trekkers walk on undulating grassy ridges with panoramic views and no trees. The lake freezes in winter and partially thaws by June, creating a spectacular ice-blue effect in early season.`,
