    description: `Lasermo La at 5,150 metres is a high pass in the Ladakh range connecting the Nubra valley with the upper Shayok region, offering one of the most dramatic and rarely trekked high-altitude crossing experiences in Ladakh. The trail climbs from the sand dunes and poplar groves of the Nubra valley through increasingly barren mountain desert to the exposed pass, with views extending over the Karakoram to the north and the Ladakh range to the south. The descent into the Shayok valley reveals a landscape of extraordinary colour — iron-red mountains, turquoise streams, and white glacier tongues. A Nubra Valley permit is required and the route is suitable only for experienced trekkers with full camping support.`,
