    description: `Kolahoi Glacier feeds the Lidder river and lies beneath the spectacular Kolahoi peak (5,425 m) — the highest mountain in the Kashmir valley. The trek from Aru climbs through the widening Lidder valley, past a series of increasingly dramatic glacial lakes and moraine landscapes, to the glacier snout at 3,830 metres. The Kolahoi peak's north face rises with extraordinary verticality above the glacier, creating one of the most dramatic mountain backdrops in Kashmir. The valley meadows in July and August are carpeted with wildflowers. This is one of Kashmir's finest glacier approach routes — accessible, scenically exceptional, and offering a genuine mountain grandeur that rivals far more demanding routes.`,
